<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 8: TIMING GEAR TRAIN AND FRONT COVER -
        GEAR TRAIN INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>GEAR TRAIN INSTALLATION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
            <title>IDLER GEARS</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">When an engine has been disassembled and the camshaft, crankshaft or idler gear removed,
                    the gears must be assembled with the timing marks properly aligned, as shown in
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600824">8.24</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The single punch marks on the crankshaft and lower idler gear and camshaft and upper idler
                            gear must align, while the two punch marks on both the idler gears must align.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Once assembled at "marks aligned" position, engine will require 37 crankshaft revolutions
                            for "marks aligned" position again.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the lower idler gear as follows (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600825">8.25</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ):
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the gear with the timing marks facing out.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Align crankshaft and lower idler gear timing marks.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Tighten the retaining bolt to the special torque value.</para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>AFTER INSTALLATION, REMEASURE CRANKSHAFT TO IDLER GEAR BACKLASH TO CONFIRM PROPER
                                assembly.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                    <figure id="ef1600824" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5313" filename="../figeg5/eg5313.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.24 Aligning Of Timing Marks</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1 type="arabic">1. Camshaft Gear</callout1>
                            <callout1 type="arabic">2. Upper Idler Gear</callout1>
                            <callout1 type="arabic">3. Crankshaft Gear</callout1>
                            <callout1 type="arabic">4. Lower Idler Gear</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1600825" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5317" filename="../figeg5/eg5317.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.25 Installing Lower Idler Gear</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the upper idler gear as follows (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600826">8.26</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ):
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>A NEW UPPER IDLER GEAR BOLT MUST BE USED AT EACH INSTALLATION OF UPPER IDLER GEAR.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the gear with the timing marks facing out.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Align camshaft, upper idler and lower idler gear timing marks.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Tighten the retaining bolt to the special torque value.</para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>REMEASURE CAMSHAFT TO IDLER GEAR BACKLASH AFTER INSTALLATION TO CONFIRM PROPER
                                Assembly.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the high pressure pump into the rear cover.
                    <emph type="underscr">BE SURE</emph>
                    to use a new gasket. Secure to rear cover with mounting bolts.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>REMEASURE HIGH PRESSURE PUMP TO UPPER IDLER GEAR BACKLASH AFTER INSTALLATION TO CONFIRM
                            PROPER Assembly.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place a new O-Ring onto the oil pressure relief valve and install the valve into the
                    crankcase (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600827">8.27</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1600826" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5315" filename="../figeg5/eg5315.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8.26 Installing Upper Idler Gear</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600827" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5305" filename="../figeg5/eg5305.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8.27 Installing Oil Pressure Relief Valve</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
